  "text": "Note that in Definition 2.3, a semimodule stands for a left L-semimodule or a right L-semimodule as in [CITATION_1] . Elements of an L-semilinear space will be called vectors and elements of a semiring scalars. The former will be denoted by bold letters to distinguish them from scalars.",
